<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf66e78f1-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s4106"><num value="4106">§ 4106.</num><heading> Penalties</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">If a vessel to which this chapter applies is operated in violation of this chapter or a regulation prescribed under this chapter, the owner, charterer, managing operator, agent, master, and individual in charge are each liable to the United States Government for a civil penalty of not more than $5,000. The vessel also is liable in rem for the penalty.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf66e78f2-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/529">97 Stat. 529</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/100/540/s3">Pub. L. 100–540, § 3</ref>, <date date="1988-10-28">Oct. 28, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/2719">102 Stat. 2719</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
